We derive an intent-explicit structured representation (SR) that captures the complete information need. Table (ref) shows such an SR for {{2204.11677_FO0020||FO}} of our running example.
SRs are frame-like structures for a question that contain designated slots for open-vocabulary lexical representations of entities in the conversational context (marked \textcolor{gray}{gray}) and the current question (\textcolor{red}{red}), relational predicates (\textcolor{blue}{blue}), and expected answer types (\textcolor{cyan}{cyan}).